title: IGI Securities Limited - Investor Kit
body: Pakistan and China are set to sign the Free Trade Agreement (FTA)-II when Prime Minister Imran Khan will leave for Beijing on April 27 for three days wherein he will also attend the second OBOR (One Belt One Road) Forum for International Corporations. The much-awaited FTA-II, once it is signed, will help Pakistan double its exports to China, Razzak Dawood, Adviser to PM on Commerce, Textile, Industry and Production and Investment, told The News in an exclusive interview. https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/451559-pakistan-to-seek-1-bn-export-orders-from-china-razak
